WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:18.020
﻿Plasma Youth Sports Games
with Unsuccess of the champion,

00:00:18.165 --> 00:00:20.525
would like to thank Slaven Bilić
for stepping in as the host.

00:00:20.648 --> 00:00:23.128
Bilić is one of the first sponsors,
ambassador and is our biggest promoter.

00:00:23.257 --> 00:00:25.862
He used his life and sports experience
in order to prepare high-quality content

00:00:25.948 --> 00:00:27.811
with his guests for all generations.
Thanks, Nane!

00:00:30.460 --> 00:00:36.100
So, Inter. You yourself said
what you had already achieved.

00:00:36.340 --> 00:00:39.940
You had results behind you.
You also had influence.

00:00:40.460 --> 00:00:44.620
And now titles… And financially,
things were the way they were.

00:00:44.820 --> 00:00:48.837
My God, they were excellent.
-But this is a series. -One moment...

00:00:48.948 --> 00:00:53.748
Sorry... -And the coach likes you.
Why did you leave Inter?

00:00:53.855 --> 00:00:56.935
Did you leave because of that
Champions League match

00:00:57.029 --> 00:00:59.469
when they kind of "called you out"?

00:00:59.575 --> 00:01:02.175
That was after the match
against Manchester United?

00:01:02.275 --> 00:01:04.395
I watched that match too,
and you were eliminated

00:01:04.495 --> 00:01:06.895
from the Champions League.
I think it happened in the quarterfinals.

00:01:07.016 --> 00:01:09.259
That’s right. -I think the result was 2:0.

00:01:10.171 --> 00:01:12.731
The fans turned a bit against you
and against Mourinho,

00:01:12.839 --> 00:01:15.564
who was brought in precisely
because of the Champions League.

00:01:15.722 --> 00:01:20.314
Why did you leave Inter, where you
were loved, it’s a big club,

00:01:20.481 --> 00:01:24.481
you were the main player there,
Milan is a beautiful city. -Yes.

00:01:24.620 --> 00:01:28.580
Why did you leave Inter? Are you a maverick
or do you just love challenges?

00:01:28.686 --> 00:01:32.566
Or did you leave because of money?
-No. It wasn’t about money.

00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:35.640
However, money is made
when transfers happen, right?

00:01:35.895 --> 00:01:38.655
Yes and no. It’s not
that simple to explain.

00:01:38.769 --> 00:01:42.649
When a big transfer happens,
the player doesn’t get all the money.

00:01:42.835 --> 00:01:44.595
As you said all this…

00:01:44.763 --> 00:01:49.523
If Inter has to allow a player
to move to another club,

00:01:49.693 --> 00:01:51.533
they will demand money.

00:01:51.663 --> 00:01:54.423
And that money doesn’t go to the player,
even though he wants to leave.

00:01:54.609 --> 00:01:59.113
If you want to change clubs...
-Money is made during transfers...

00:01:59.291 --> 00:02:05.014
Clubs earn the most money when they pay
less for a player than he’s worth.

00:02:05.325 --> 00:02:08.186
In my case, it was approximately
the same transfer fee.

00:02:08.331 --> 00:02:10.377
But everyone wants Ibrahimović.

00:02:10.516 --> 00:02:14.295
And the football agent gets a percentage
of the player’s salary. -That’s right.

00:02:14.451 --> 00:02:16.730
And I already had that
same salary at Inter.

00:02:16.835 --> 00:02:19.235
My salary didn’t increase
when I moved to Barcelona.

00:02:19.296 --> 00:02:22.420
I continued receiving the same salary.
-Okay, then why did you leave Inter?

00:02:22.566 --> 00:02:27.766
I left because Barcelona
was the best club at that time.

00:02:27.914 --> 00:02:30.714
Guardiola was great,
but Mourinho was great too.

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:34.319
However, Barcelona as a team,
the way they played,

00:02:34.492 --> 00:02:36.212
for me, all of that was new.

00:02:36.319 --> 00:02:39.999
I received an offer
from Barcelona to join them.

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:43.240
That year they had won
the Champions League as well.

00:02:43.464 --> 00:02:48.827
Thinking about it, I came to the conclusion
that I had been at Inter for three years,

00:02:48.953 --> 00:02:52.694
I won the Scudetto three times
in a row, two Italian Super Cups.

00:02:52.907 --> 00:02:54.907
I decided I wanted a new challenge.

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:58.710
To go to Spain and play
for Barcelona or Real Madrid.

00:02:58.963 --> 00:03:02.043
Barcelona sent me an offer first,
and I decided to go there to see

00:03:02.159 --> 00:03:04.759
for myself what kind of football
is played in La Liga.

00:03:04.914 --> 00:03:07.897
At that time, Barcelona had
excellent footballers.

00:03:08.045 --> 00:03:10.485
I decided to move to Barcelona
to prove to myself whether

00:03:10.607 --> 00:03:12.893
I was really that good a footballer.

00:03:13.037 --> 00:03:16.791
What kind of player am I? I didn’t want
to stay in my comfort zone anymore.

00:03:16.969 --> 00:03:23.010
I decided to pack my bags
and go to another country

00:03:23.135 --> 00:03:25.111
and play in a new stadium.

00:03:25.333 --> 00:03:29.321
I decided to prove myself
in another country.

00:03:31.434 --> 00:03:35.546
So, the fact that I was
the best at Inter and all that...

00:03:35.720 --> 00:03:39.223
I could have stayed at Inter
and continued being the best,

00:03:39.543 --> 00:03:44.983
but I chose to leave and try
everything again from scratch

00:03:45.164 --> 00:03:47.364
in another country.

00:03:47.472 --> 00:03:50.872
Bravo. -And because
of that decision I suffered a bit.

00:03:51.081 --> 00:03:58.441
And I realized the following:
"Maybe it’s better for a dream

00:03:58.820 --> 00:04:03.500
to remain a dream than to come true.
Because a dream can kill you."

00:04:03.660 --> 00:04:06.138
Can you translate that?
-I understood you.

00:04:06.315 --> 00:04:09.372
How do you say "dream"?
-Dream.

00:04:09.489 --> 00:04:12.969
Maybe it’s better for a dream
to stay just a dream...

00:04:13.450 --> 00:04:16.330
Because if you realize it...

00:04:16.508 --> 00:04:21.404
Because if a dream comes true,
it might be bad for me.

00:04:21.732 --> 00:04:23.780
That’s why I was no longer happy.

00:04:24.420 --> 00:04:27.900
My dream was to move to Barcelona.
But because of that dream,

00:04:28.100 --> 00:04:31.980
I didn’t feel good. I was
no longer as happy as before.

00:04:32.180 --> 00:04:39.245
Because the newspapers published
an article before my move to Barcelona,

00:04:39.359 --> 00:04:41.759
saying that my character
wasn’t good for the club.

00:04:41.841 --> 00:04:43.554
That I was different.
-You’re special.

00:04:43.652 --> 00:04:46.003
It took me back to the time
when I played for Malmö,

00:04:46.106 --> 00:04:48.026
and I felt different again.

00:04:48.143 --> 00:04:51.875
I said to myself: "You’re spending
too much time thinking."

00:04:52.014 --> 00:04:55.614
I always had to think twice
before doing something.

00:04:56.409 --> 00:05:01.234
And I did that so that people
in Barcelona would like me.

00:05:01.390 --> 00:05:05.060
Now we’ll go back to when we talked
about what makes a great player.

00:05:05.300 --> 00:05:09.740
A player is great when he behaves
the way he believes he should behave.

00:05:09.980 --> 00:05:13.100
But at that time, I was trying
to be something I wasn’t.

00:05:13.300 --> 00:05:18.180
I wanted people to like me
because journalists were writing

00:05:18.420 --> 00:05:21.460
that I wasn’t a player for Barcelona.

00:05:21.597 --> 00:05:24.357
You don’t fit in.
-I behaved differently.

00:05:24.477 --> 00:05:26.703
I didn’t behave the same way
I did when I arrived at Juventus,

00:05:26.860 --> 00:05:30.740
where I only thought about
the game and how to win.

00:05:30.940 --> 00:05:32.819
In Barcelona, I was more...

00:05:32.960 --> 00:05:35.440
On the first day, Guardiola told me
that Barcelona players don’t come

00:05:35.545 --> 00:05:37.498
to training in a Ferrari.

00:05:37.711 --> 00:05:42.038
I thought, what is he trying to tell me?
I just want to be who I am.

00:05:42.148 --> 00:05:45.483
Whether I arrive in a Ferrari or not,
what does that change?

00:05:45.637 --> 00:05:47.477
How does that affect me?

00:05:47.660 --> 00:05:52.233
Okay, I accepted that, and every time
I wanted to make a decision,

00:05:52.350 --> 00:05:54.905
I had to think twice.
That wasn’t right.

00:05:55.038 --> 00:06:01.030
So, how you feel off the pitch
is how you’ll feel on the pitch.

00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:04.080
You’re right.
-You carry that experience.

00:06:04.147 --> 00:06:06.350
How you feel off the pitch
is how you’ll feel on the pitch.

00:06:06.453 --> 00:06:08.928
If you don’t feel good off the pitch,
you won’t feel good on it either.

00:06:09.038 --> 00:06:11.300
Of course. -That’s rule number one.

00:06:11.414 --> 00:06:16.116
The first six months went well,
I played and scored goals.

00:06:16.357 --> 00:06:19.572
I had good cooperation with Guardiola,
and then something happened…

00:06:19.860 --> 00:06:24.620
I don’t know. To this day,
he never told me what it was about.

00:06:24.860 --> 00:06:30.060
From that moment on,
I didn’t play for the next six months.

00:06:30.166 --> 00:06:33.206
And I’m not the type of player
who goes to the coach and asks:

00:06:33.305 --> 00:06:35.260
"Why am I not playing?"

00:06:35.407 --> 00:06:41.660
Before, when situations like this
happened with coaches, it gave me

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:43.640
more motivation to be better.

00:06:44.593 --> 00:06:50.319
I don’t get angry at the coach;
it motivates me to improve.

00:06:50.831 --> 00:06:55.085
Then one, two, three, four matches
passed without me playing.

00:06:55.292 --> 00:06:59.952
It was no longer about the way
I played, but about something else.

00:07:00.154 --> 00:07:03.350
People from the club advised me
to talk to Guardiola.

00:07:03.471 --> 00:07:06.671
To initiate a conversation with him
so that the club could get involved

00:07:06.768 --> 00:07:08.904
and help resolve the problem.

00:07:09.061 --> 00:07:11.101
Because for them,
I was a big investment.

00:07:11.262 --> 00:07:14.742
They had to pay 70 million for my transfer.
That’s why I mentioned the commission.

00:07:15.004 --> 00:07:19.084
To allow me to move
from Inter to Barcelona,

00:07:19.214 --> 00:07:22.116
they had to pay a huge
amount of money.

00:07:22.240 --> 00:07:24.138
That’s right, 70 million
and the deal is done.

00:07:24.270 --> 00:07:26.520
Give us 70 million and no problem.

00:07:26.647 --> 00:07:29.847
They told me: "If you want to go,
it has to be paid."

00:07:30.049 --> 00:07:33.409
It wasn’t: you want it
and I just want my commission.

00:07:33.570 --> 00:07:38.410
Better stay at Inter. That’s why I
mentioned the agent’s commission.

00:07:38.641 --> 00:07:41.721
It was expensive.
No doubt about that. -Of course.

00:07:42.040 --> 00:07:43.800
But I agreed to it.

00:07:44.025 --> 00:07:49.105
After that situation, when I stopped
playing matches at Barcelona,

00:07:49.540 --> 00:07:53.180
I decided to go to Guardiola,
and before starting the conversation

00:07:53.420 --> 00:07:56.700
I told him this: "I didn’t come
here to cause problems.

00:07:56.940 --> 00:08:00.260
You’re the coach, you’re the boss.

00:08:00.500 --> 00:08:03.420
Whatever you decide,
that’s how it will be.

00:08:03.620 --> 00:08:08.060
I’ll respect your decisions,
but I also have my own conditions

00:08:08.260 --> 00:08:14.140
that need to be met so I can help you
and the team as much as possible."

00:08:14.780 --> 00:08:20.578
I told him: "I think you’re
sacrificing me for other players."

00:08:20.766 --> 00:08:25.140
I need space to show what I can do.
-You need space.

00:08:25.340 --> 00:08:27.060
Otherwise, what am I doing here?

00:08:27.300 --> 00:08:31.620
It’s better for you to have
other players, and I’ll move on.

00:08:32.460 --> 00:08:36.660
We talked for about an hour,
and in the end I told him:

00:08:36.860 --> 00:08:41.051
"I don’t want to cause problems,
I’m a professional,

00:08:41.142 --> 00:08:42.862
I want to keep training."

00:08:43.039 --> 00:08:45.999
He replied: "No problem,
I’ll take care of that."

00:08:46.980 --> 00:08:50.300
After that, I was still only
on the bench.

00:08:50.580 --> 00:08:54.100
After that conversation,
I didn’t understand

00:08:54.340 --> 00:08:58.660
what it was about, and he never
explained it to me later either.

00:08:58.900 --> 00:09:02.300
After six months passed
since that conversation,

00:09:02.540 --> 00:09:05.260
I no longer felt happy.
He took away...

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:09.500
You know how it is
when you play football,

00:09:09.740 --> 00:09:12.860
when you step onto the pitch,
you feel something different,

00:09:13.060 --> 00:09:14.980
you feel alive, you play.
-That’s right.

00:09:15.180 --> 00:09:20.500
A teammate passes you the ball,
you pass it to another player...

00:09:20.740 --> 00:09:23.740
You move around the pitch,
you talk... -You feel happy.

00:09:23.940 --> 00:09:26.220
That’s when a player feels
completely different,

00:09:26.420 --> 00:09:27.860
and he took all that away from me.

00:09:28.060 --> 00:09:30.940
After that, I didn’t even feel
like training, nor did I want to be

00:09:31.180 --> 00:09:34.820
at Barcelona anymore.
I felt different from the other players.

00:09:35.060 --> 00:09:39.380
He made me feel unwelcome.
And that’s not right.

00:09:39.860 --> 00:09:42.140
I felt like I was in someone
else’s house.

00:09:42.340 --> 00:09:51.100
I didn’t feel good anymore
and I stopped enjoying football.

00:09:51.820 --> 00:09:54.020
You stopped enjoying it.

00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:58.180
After that conversation, the next day
I came to training in a Ferrari.

00:09:58.380 --> 00:10:01.500
And I parked it in front of his office.

00:10:02.940 --> 00:10:06.260
It was a situation where
one ego was fighting another.

00:10:06.460 --> 00:10:11.660
It was a sign of disrespect,
you did it intentionally.

00:10:11.900 --> 00:10:15.100
We no longer had normal communication.
-You wanted to show him who you were.

00:10:15.340 --> 00:10:17.620
Exactly. Because I also
have my own identity.

00:10:17.820 --> 00:10:19.900
I gave everything I had,
but it wasn’t enough.

00:10:20.140 --> 00:10:22.140
After that, I wanted
to prove who I really was.

00:10:22.340 --> 00:10:24.740
I no longer wanted to think twice
before saying something.

00:10:24.940 --> 00:10:26.900
From that moment on,
I was my true self.

00:10:27.140 --> 00:10:29.660
I continued training, but I came
to training the way I wanted.

00:10:29.900 --> 00:10:32.580
We continued like that.
The season came to an end,

00:10:32.780 --> 00:10:34.780
and we were champions.

00:10:34.980 --> 00:10:38.900
In the Champions League, we lost
the semifinal match against Inter.

00:10:39.100 --> 00:10:43.140
That’s right... -Before I left...
Mourinho, Mourinho. -That was the worst.

00:10:43.340 --> 00:10:46.860
Before my move to Barcelona,
I talked to Mourinho and told him:

00:10:47.060 --> 00:10:51.540
"I’m moving to Barcelona and..."
He replied: "Where are you going?"

00:10:51.740 --> 00:10:54.780
I said: "I’m going to Barcelona."
He said: "No, you’re not."

00:10:55.020 --> 00:10:57.620
I replied: "Yes, I am."
I’m going to Barcelona.

00:10:57.820 --> 00:10:59.940
He asked me:
"Why are you going?"

00:11:00.180 --> 00:11:02.220
I replied: "Because I want to
win the Champions League."

00:11:02.420 --> 00:11:04.500
Before I left, he told me this:
"Listen, this year we’ll be

00:11:04.740 --> 00:11:10.420
the winners, not Barcelona."
-Yes, yes. -And Inter really did win.

00:11:10.740 --> 00:11:15.260
But what had to happen, happened.
A year earlier, he told me they would win.

00:11:15.500 --> 00:11:21.420
I have to congratulate him on that.
-Incredible... -That’s how it all happened...

00:11:22.980 --> 00:11:27.060
And then after Barcelona, I moved
to Milan. That’s how it happened.

00:11:27.300 --> 00:11:32.780
After Barcelona, you don’t go
to Inter, but to Milan.

00:11:33.020 --> 00:11:37.100
And you win the league again
with Allegri, right? -That’s right.

00:11:37.340 --> 00:11:42.460
You played for the three biggest
clubs in Italy: Juventus, Inter, and Milan.

00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:49.900
A man needs great confidence and courage
to move from one club to another.

00:11:50.180 --> 00:11:52.980
Because fans in Italy
are very temperamental. -Very.

00:11:53.180 --> 00:11:56.260
How did Inter fans accept you
at first, or later Milan fans?

00:11:56.460 --> 00:11:58.420
Since you changed those three clubs.

00:11:58.660 --> 00:12:05.700
At that time, Milan hadn’t won
the Italian league for two years.

00:12:06.300 --> 00:12:11.700
Players like Gattuso, Pirlo, Nesta...
-Seedorf. -Zambrotta, Seedorf...

00:12:12.740 --> 00:12:16.420
They were all players
at the end of their careers.

00:12:16.620 --> 00:12:20.220
And they needed
someone who would...

00:12:20.620 --> 00:12:24.460
Who would bring out
the last bit of strength...

00:12:24.700 --> 00:12:27.500
Who would bring out
the last bit of strength in them.

00:12:27.660 --> 00:12:29.420
Because they were already veterans.

00:12:29.620 --> 00:12:32.660
They themselves said that Ibra
was the one who could help them.

00:12:32.900 --> 00:12:35.540
The situation was this: either they
win the league or they leave Milan.

00:12:35.780 --> 00:12:43.500
I came to Milan at a time when
I wasn’t happy playing football.

00:12:43.700 --> 00:12:48.580
I came to Milan and they gave me...
-The desire you needed.

00:12:48.820 --> 00:12:54.860
The desire to play. After that,
I started playing at Milan

00:12:55.100 --> 00:12:57.460
and once again had that feeling
that I was alive.

00:12:57.700 --> 00:12:59.540
And you were the league’s
top scorer again, right?

00:12:59.780 --> 00:13:04.100
Yes, I was the top scorer.
-It was great.

00:13:04.300 --> 00:13:06.420
There were great players in the club.

00:13:06.542 --> 00:13:09.982
And the club itself was...
-Huge. - ...the best of the best.

00:13:10.199 --> 00:13:14.919
So why did you leave Milan?
Why move to Paris?

00:13:15.096 --> 00:13:18.684
I didn’t want to leave Milan.
-You didn’t want to? -That’s the difference.

00:13:18.839 --> 00:13:21.433
That was the first time
I didn’t want to go.

00:13:21.636 --> 00:13:25.638
But they sold me because they
needed money. -And Thiago Silva.

00:13:25.817 --> 00:13:29.937
They sold both of us at the same time.

00:13:30.114 --> 00:13:34.634
You left at the same time.
-It wasn’t my wish. My wish was to stay.

00:13:34.982 --> 00:13:40.955
Before that, I had a meeting with
Galliani after winning the title sorry,

00:13:41.127 --> 00:13:43.683
that year we didn’t win the title.

00:13:43.919 --> 00:13:48.943
I told him: "Listen, when the summer
transfer window comes,

00:13:49.093 --> 00:13:53.080
my wish is to stay at Milan.
Because I feel good here.

00:13:53.338 --> 00:13:58.573
I was in Barcelona, where some
ugly things happened to me.

00:13:59.005 --> 00:14:03.204
I don’t want to leave Milan
because I feel good here.

00:14:03.500 --> 00:14:07.420
I’m happy playing and I don’t
want to change that."

00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:09.510
He replied: "Okay, no problem."

00:14:09.709 --> 00:14:15.149
Three weeks after that conversation,
I got a call from Mino.

00:14:15.780 --> 00:14:21.740
It was immediately clear to me what it was
about. Everything was clear. Paris.

00:14:21.948 --> 00:14:26.788
Four years, right? -Four years in
Paris... I didn't want to go to Paris.

00:14:27.020 --> 00:14:31.860
I said I'd rather play here in front of
80.000 people in a stadium, in Serie A.

00:14:32.020 --> 00:14:38.820
What I wanted to say earlier, when
I arrived in Serie A, it was top-tier;

00:14:39.060 --> 00:14:47.145
all the best, most prominent players
were there. Many were fighting to win...

00:14:47.420 --> 00:14:54.340
And then the Premier League was more...
-It was becoming...

00:14:54.469 --> 00:14:56.405
Yeah, yeah, it was starting...

00:14:56.567 --> 00:14:58.968
Serie A eventually got overtaken
by the Premier League...

00:14:59.153 --> 00:15:02.906
That's why I can say, Serie A
used to be... -The biggest. -Top, top...

00:15:03.503 --> 00:15:06.296
And then I went to Paris and asked them
what I was supposed to do there.

00:15:06.369 --> 00:15:09.187
I was going to play in a stadium
with only 5.000 people.

00:15:09.306 --> 00:15:13.187
That's the honest truth. I said, "Here I
have 80.000, and now I'm going somewhere

00:15:13.378 --> 00:15:18.750
with 5.000, it's not like an upgrade;
it felt like I was downgrading."

00:15:19.133 --> 00:15:24.945
And then they explained their project,
what they wanted and thought,

00:15:25.133 --> 00:15:30.853
and that they wanted to invest,
build a team, and everything...

00:15:31.140 --> 00:15:39.460
And then Milan, no, Mino pressured me,
saying Milan wouldn't be the same...

00:15:40.460 --> 00:15:44.428
He was right. -He was right.
-Yeah, he was right.

00:15:44.553 --> 00:15:47.473
In the previous 10 years, they hadn't
played in the Champions League. -Bravo.

00:15:47.688 --> 00:15:51.842
Everything was changing,
and Mino seemed to see everything.

00:15:52.420 --> 00:15:57.500
And Paris kept improving.
It was getting better and better.

00:15:57.900 --> 00:16:02.660
And everything we did led to
today's result, to this victory.

00:16:02.860 --> 00:16:07.100
Now with Luis Enrique...
But you're the one, you're the first...

00:16:07.300 --> 00:16:15.140
I was in Paris when
it wasn't the club it is today.

00:16:15.660 --> 00:16:20.380
Back then, the situation was totally
different from what it is now.

00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:24.020
Your impact is more substantial because
of that. Your impact was strongest then.

00:16:24.260 --> 00:16:30.100
That was my challenge: to lift the club,
to make it world-class,

00:16:30.380 --> 00:16:35.420
to shape that mentality,
and to reach a level through results.

00:16:35.620 --> 00:16:40.500
Level up or two levels up. -Yes, yes.
Players that come in now have it easy.

00:16:40.740 --> 00:16:43.020
They now have the biggest
training ground in the world.

00:16:43.190 --> 00:16:45.350
Players are now begging
to be bought by Paris.

00:16:45.489 --> 00:16:48.169
The club doesn't even need
to pay them that much anymore.

00:16:48.420 --> 00:16:54.380
I told Nasser, for every project
you need an architect,

00:16:54.740 --> 00:16:57.380
and for this one, I was the architect.

00:16:57.580 --> 00:17:01.660
I built PSG as a club, everyone that
comes in now gets to eat caviar.

00:17:01.820 --> 00:17:04.602
When I was there,
I was eating schnitzel.

00:17:04.830 --> 00:17:07.281
And what about when they say...

00:17:07.444 --> 00:17:10.284
But they're good, they're good,
they're grateful. They're very grateful.

00:17:10.454 --> 00:17:13.214
Nasser is good.
-Nasser is exceptional. -Yes, yes.

00:17:13.611 --> 00:17:17.141
And do you know where else your
influence is visible?

00:17:17.282 --> 00:17:19.762
Because your perception is often
that you have this ego

00:17:19.916 --> 00:17:22.670
and you don't tolerate
someone being close to you,

00:17:22.845 --> 00:17:25.365
but you accepted Beckham to come,
and Beckham is like the Beatles...

00:17:25.537 --> 00:17:29.191
Yes, yes, he's great. -That's PR...
And you didn't just accept him...

00:17:29.314 --> 00:17:32.011
You also decide who can come, right?
You suggest things?

00:17:32.131 --> 00:17:35.253
They don't ask, but there's
a conversation. -You're important.

00:17:35.438 --> 00:17:38.118
In the end, it's important
who the coach and the club want,

00:17:38.232 --> 00:17:40.457
it's not about asking the player
if he wants to come.

00:17:40.571 --> 00:17:42.971
You give some suggestions...
-They already have...

00:17:43.110 --> 00:17:47.590
There's a strategy,
what they want from the team.

00:17:47.910 --> 00:17:53.097
I think they brought Beckham in for
six months to finish his career there.

00:17:53.260 --> 00:17:56.500
Yes. -They didn't bring him
just for his football skills,

00:17:56.599 --> 00:17:59.439
but for the whole package
that comes with him.

00:17:59.592 --> 00:18:03.668
Every day, 2.000 people stayed after
training, everyone was asking for him.

00:18:03.835 --> 00:18:05.996
It's a totally different situation...

00:18:06.233 --> 00:18:11.965
I think, with this ego, when you're
a player at the start of your career,

00:18:12.149 --> 00:18:16.909
you have more ego for yourself, and then
as you approach the end of your career,

00:18:17.110 --> 00:18:21.110
you no longer have that ego just
for yourself, but for everyone else,

00:18:21.358 --> 00:18:26.518
because at the beginning you take
for yourself and later give to others.

00:18:27.900 --> 00:18:29.780
In the end...

00:18:31.460 --> 00:18:37.900
When I turned 29 or 30, even 28,
I didn't have ego just for myself,

00:18:38.100 --> 00:18:40.660
because I knew who I was
and what I'd done...

00:18:40.860 --> 00:18:43.780
You proved yourself to be
a proven player... -I proved it...

00:18:43.886 --> 00:18:47.406
I didn't need to prove myself anymore,
I just needed to deliver results.

00:18:47.543 --> 00:18:50.677
Yes, yes. -And in the end,
I gave everything back to the team.

00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:54.660
It wasn't about me anymore,
I was in a situation like Modrić now.

00:18:54.852 --> 00:18:59.932
It's no longer about him... -Stability.
-He does things for others. -Yes, bravo.

00:19:00.077 --> 00:19:04.597
He showed the way to others.
He's an example to others.

00:19:04.900 --> 00:19:08.100
He showed and helped others,
the new generation.

00:19:08.340 --> 00:19:12.020
I was in the same situation
when I came here...

00:19:12.220 --> 00:19:15.060
That's why I say that in the beginning,

00:19:15.260 --> 00:19:17.940
egomania is very present
because a lot is on you,

00:19:18.180 --> 00:19:24.460
you want to prove yourself,
you want more, new club, bigger club,

00:19:24.700 --> 00:19:28.340
you do everything for yourself.
When you reach a certain level,

00:19:28.580 --> 00:19:31.580
then it's just about the results
and giving back to those around you.

00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:34.620
If you realize yourself as a player,
if you reach that level, of course.

00:19:34.860 --> 00:19:37.460
Everyone has their own destiny.

00:19:38.180 --> 00:19:42.180
And from Paris, in 2016,
you go to the island, right? -Yes.

00:19:42.389 --> 00:19:44.971
To the Premier League,
again with Mourinho,

00:19:45.140 --> 00:19:49.740
and it was an excellent season,
maybe the best season after Ferguson,

00:19:49.940 --> 00:19:53.500
but at that time, they were obsessed
with needing more, more, more...

00:19:53.700 --> 00:19:58.620
But you won three trophies. -We went
to United because Mourinho called me,

00:19:58.820 --> 00:20:02.580
I told him I would go
because I was good with him.

00:20:02.820 --> 00:20:07.780
As I said, when he has a player,
he manipulates and has a feel for them,

00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:13.060
maybe because of everything on the field...
He called me to come to United.

00:20:13.300 --> 00:20:17.420
I asked him, why should I go
to the Premier League?

00:20:17.700 --> 00:20:22.340
I just asked because I was curious.
-You were curious.

00:20:22.660 --> 00:20:28.060
I asked five players
I had played with before,

00:20:28.420 --> 00:20:33.700
what would you do if you got an offer
from a Premier League club?

00:20:33.862 --> 00:20:36.102
All five of them told me not to go.

00:20:36.295 --> 00:20:38.655
Not to go? -Yes, yes,
they told me not to go.

00:20:38.777 --> 00:20:42.747
But why? Because I would be
risking everything I achieved

00:20:42.940 --> 00:20:45.580
by going to the Premier League.

00:20:45.702 --> 00:20:51.263
If I don't perform well there,
all that I achieved loses its value.

00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:54.780
It loses its value, you are judged
by what you do in Premier league. -Bravo.

00:20:55.540 --> 00:20:59.060
I told them, perfect, I'm going to
the Premier League. -Challenge, right?

00:20:59.300 --> 00:21:02.860
Yes. I couldn't get it out
of my head and decided to put

00:21:03.045 --> 00:21:06.845
all 20 years of my career
on the line in the Premier League.

00:21:07.097 --> 00:21:12.097
Everything I achieved in Inter,
Juventus, Milan... -Paris, Barcelona...

00:21:12.203 --> 00:21:14.323
Paris... I put everything at stake
in the Premier League.

00:21:14.406 --> 00:21:19.086
I was 35 years old at the time.
That's what kept me going, gave me energy.

00:21:19.341 --> 00:21:25.141
Now it wasn't just about
a good contract giving me motivation,

00:21:25.372 --> 00:21:29.572
now, it was about who I am,
my personality... That was also at play.

00:21:29.720 --> 00:21:34.627
Personality, pride, yes... -Pride,
legacy, which is extremely important.

00:21:34.804 --> 00:21:38.604
Of course. -I'm going to put everything,
like in roulette, on one number.

00:21:38.727 --> 00:21:42.847
20 years of my career on Manchester.
I went there and...

00:21:43.071 --> 00:21:50.455
In every club I'd been before,
except for Barcelona, I trained alone.

00:21:50.947 --> 00:21:55.220
I had that mentality,
order and discipline.

00:21:55.608 --> 00:22:03.528
Mourinho gave me enough space.
He worked as a coach, and we as players.

00:22:05.380 --> 00:22:08.660
Every training session was intense.

00:22:08.900 --> 00:22:13.100
I arrived there, and everyone said
they had no chance in the Premier League,

00:22:13.300 --> 00:22:16.900
that it moves fast, everything is...

00:22:17.550 --> 00:22:23.270
Football in the Premier League...
That rhythm is a whole different story.

00:22:23.517 --> 00:22:29.772
Well, I took my things, went to them.
It's not that they came to me,

00:22:30.053 --> 00:22:32.842
I went to them to show myself.

00:22:33.642 --> 00:22:37.010
It's different, when I talk about
loyalty, it's not loyalty...

00:22:37.206 --> 00:22:40.926
I was looking to see how far I could go,
and then, if you survive,

00:22:41.151 --> 00:22:44.871
as you said, not everyone makes it...
I wanted to try.

00:22:45.023 --> 00:22:49.608
If I didn't try, I would always
wonder what could have happened.

00:22:49.780 --> 00:22:51.620
It wasn't about that...
It's better to go there...

00:22:51.781 --> 00:22:57.061
Whether I win or not, at least I have
an answer to the question "what if."

00:22:57.300 --> 00:23:02.020
Exactly. -I wasn't good, or I was good.
I went there, and after three months,

00:23:02.166 --> 00:23:05.126
I already had the whole
Premier League in my pocket.

00:23:05.413 --> 00:23:09.173
After just three months
because of the way I played.

00:23:09.540 --> 00:23:13.500
Manchester United hadn't been
a good club for a long time...

00:23:13.740 --> 00:23:16.540
At the end of the year, I got injured.

00:23:16.740 --> 00:23:20.420
There was only one month left, and
I got injured, but I won three trophies.

00:23:20.620 --> 00:23:23.060
Three trophies and got
injured, unfortunately...

00:23:23.260 --> 00:23:26.500
If Arsenal wins...
I managed to win more in one year

00:23:26.660 --> 00:23:31.540
than they did in the last 15 years.
-Did you tell Pires that?

00:23:31.709 --> 00:23:34.989
I'm saying it now. So it's a bit...

00:23:35.820 --> 00:23:39.780
So, Manchester United fans are
singing songs about you and everything...

00:23:39.980 --> 00:23:41.700
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
but it was a different thing...

00:23:41.900 --> 00:23:44.260
You were in these... Is that...

00:23:44.460 --> 00:23:47.340
The Premier League is
a whole different thing.

00:23:47.580 --> 00:23:49.260
Manchester United fans...

00:23:49.460 --> 00:23:51.100
Of course, it's said it's
the biggest club in the world,

00:23:51.300 --> 00:23:55.740
and you had the honor and quality
to play in these huge clubs that can say

00:23:55.940 --> 00:23:58.700
they are the biggest. -Yes.
-How do you view that?

00:23:58.860 --> 00:24:00.820
Is the Premier League really special?

00:24:01.020 --> 00:24:03.500
I played in Serie A
when it was the special league.

00:24:03.700 --> 00:24:06.780
The Premier League is now
the biggest league.

00:24:06.980 --> 00:24:12.020
I was in the biggest club in the Premier
League, in United, at that time...

00:24:12.300 --> 00:24:17.060
I can't say Liverpool, but for me,
it was United... -So, the biggest club...

00:24:17.260 --> 00:24:23.580
With fans... I arrived in the Premier
League, and the stadium was packed.

00:24:24.180 --> 00:24:29.860
The grass, everything was perfect.
The Manchester United fans,

00:24:30.060 --> 00:24:34.780
when I scored in the first game,
sang my name for 45 minutes,

00:24:34.980 --> 00:24:38.460
and I hadn't even played that well...
I told them, don't sing anymore,

00:24:38.700 --> 00:24:41.020
wait until I start playing well,
then you can sing...

00:24:41.260 --> 00:24:48.500
I felt weak because I wasn't playing
well, and they were giving me credit

00:24:49.060 --> 00:24:53.060
for such little effort.
I wanted to deserve that.

00:24:53.260 --> 00:24:57.540
You wanted to deserve it, yes, yes...
-... deserve their praises.

00:24:57.740 --> 00:25:02.780
I said, no, I didn't deserve this,
wait until I start playing well.

00:25:04.020 --> 00:25:08.180
And then, as the match went on...

00:25:08.420 --> 00:25:11.220
You know yourself,
a match isn't over until it's over.

00:25:11.420 --> 00:25:16.980
The last 10 minutes... Yesterday I saw
Manchester Everton 4-4. -Bournemouth...

00:25:17.180 --> 00:25:20.260
Yes, Bournemouth, sorry...
It was as if it was over, but it wasn't.

00:25:20.460 --> 00:25:23.500
Just like that, the result was 3-0,
and in the last 10 minutes,

00:25:23.740 --> 00:25:28.420
we come back to 3-3, then 4-3...
It was like I had a heart attack.

00:25:28.660 --> 00:25:31.220
In Italy, 1-0, and it was done.

00:25:32.260 --> 00:25:36.220
1-0, put me on the bus, and it's over.

00:25:36.420 --> 00:25:40.220
Capello, when he wins 1-0,
he says the match is over,

00:25:40.460 --> 00:25:43.060
I push, and he says it's done...

00:25:43.300 --> 00:25:46.500
But in the Premier League,
it was 1-0, 2-0, 3-0,

00:25:46.700 --> 00:25:51.300
now we're starting to control
the game... What about 3-1...

00:25:51.500 --> 00:25:54.060
People love that, they love it,
that's... -It's hard.

00:25:54.300 --> 00:25:56.740
I told the players,
we can't do this every match,

00:25:56.940 --> 00:25:59.980
we need to control the situation.
If we don't do that, we won't win.

00:26:00.180 --> 00:26:04.340
We need to be smart, even though
the fans love this, I love to win,

00:26:04.540 --> 00:26:07.380
and I know I'll win, but this way...

00:26:07.580 --> 00:26:13.460
we'll end up in the hospital after
three months if we keep going like this,

00:26:13.660 --> 00:26:16.340
and I'm still not ready
to end it here...

00:26:16.580 --> 00:26:19.940
But it's the best,
the Premier League is top, top, top.

00:26:20.180 --> 00:26:26.180
It's not easy, it's hard,
it's a different culture, mentality.

00:26:27.420 --> 00:26:33.020
I saw football differently. The referees
there are much more respected.

00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:36.298
A whole other thing. -It's beautiful.
Beautiful. -Very, very.

00:26:36.458 --> 00:26:40.485
That's why I say, I was there, and
I'm grateful I had the opportunity...

00:26:40.639 --> 00:26:43.079
What if I hadn't gone there?

00:26:43.273 --> 00:26:45.579
I'd always wonder how I would
have played in the Premier League?

00:26:45.711 --> 00:26:49.071
That's it. -Yes. It would have been
a shame for both sides...

00:26:49.236 --> 00:26:52.036
And in the Premier League,
some problems start, right?

00:26:52.307 --> 00:26:58.134
I injured my knee. For the first time,
I got seriously injured.

00:27:00.820 --> 00:27:04.980
That's when panic set in
because something like that

00:27:05.182 --> 00:27:08.862
had never happened to me before.
I was 36 years old at the time,

00:27:09.055 --> 00:27:12.415
and I said, I've had my entire
career, and this is how it ends...

00:27:12.583 --> 00:27:18.343
This isn't Ibra anymore.
I'm a fighter. -You're a fighter.

00:27:18.740 --> 00:27:24.500
A fighter can't end like this.
But I came to a situation

00:27:26.420 --> 00:27:31.220
where I didn't know where I was because
I'd never been in such a position.

00:27:31.420 --> 00:27:35.260
I had minor muscle injuries, cramps...
I had minor injuries...

00:27:36.180 --> 00:27:40.780
This was my first significant injury.

00:27:41.140 --> 00:27:47.300
Suddenly, my world was different.
I was on top, playing, training...

00:27:47.500 --> 00:27:52.100
And in one second,
I fell to the bottom.

00:27:52.300 --> 00:27:58.413
The next day I couldn't train,
couldn't walk, nothing...

00:27:59.740 --> 00:28:03.002
My body wanted to keep going...

00:28:04.900 --> 00:28:11.300
While I was sleeping, my body was
shaking because it wanted to train.

00:28:11.540 --> 00:28:15.900
That's normal when you train
during the season.

00:28:16.420 --> 00:28:20.100
There are breaks, but you always
do something new, you're active.

00:28:20.380 --> 00:28:24.100
I went from 100% to 0%.

00:28:24.620 --> 00:28:30.820
I got the news that my knee
was completely destroyed,

00:28:31.060 --> 00:28:36.100
that there were multiple injuries:
ACL, meniscus.

00:28:36.500 --> 00:28:41.340
The muscle popped right here,
but in my head, everything was fine.

00:28:41.540 --> 00:28:47.260
Everything was okay. The day it happened,
everyone... I was looking at the doctor,

00:28:47.780 --> 00:28:52.260
the physio, and they said it was over.
I was full of adrenaline. No, it's not.

00:28:52.460 --> 00:28:56.780
I am Ibra, I am Superman.
Nothing can happen to me.

00:28:56.980 --> 00:29:02.780
The next day, I could walk.
It was a bit swollen, but I could walk.

00:29:02.980 --> 00:29:06.820
Everything was okay.
I went for the MRI.

00:29:08.460 --> 00:29:11.460
One year. One year...

00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:20.962
Everyone said... I had the surgery.
I asked to do everything at once.

00:29:21.251 --> 00:29:27.660
Usually, when you operate on the ACL,
you wait two months, then the muscle.

00:29:27.900 --> 00:29:30.500
I wanted it all at once because...

00:29:31.300 --> 00:29:34.300
I took a risk... -For the recovery.

00:29:34.540 --> 00:29:41.420
If I tightened the leg, the muscle pops.
We'll make a strategy and a program

00:29:43.380 --> 00:29:47.260
so that everything works.
I didn't want to lose two months.

00:29:47.460 --> 00:29:51.540
I trained, I moved on,
and I got into a situation...

00:29:51.860 --> 00:29:58.300
Now, it's not... how do you say?
A challenge to play football.

00:29:58.500 --> 00:30:04.220
Now, the challenge is to come back.
To return and be the Ibra I was...

00:30:04.343 --> 00:30:06.023
Before. -Before.

00:30:06.340 --> 00:30:10.220
I don't want to play on my name alone.
If I'm Ibrahimovic and you play with me,

00:30:10.420 --> 00:30:18.260
and I don't get results, it's better...
-I get it. -I'm not helping you or me.

00:30:18.460 --> 00:30:22.260
No merit. -It doesn't work.
When it's over, it's over.

00:30:22.500 --> 00:30:31.780
Mentally, I couldn't get going,
because I had to wait for this to heal.

00:30:32.060 --> 00:30:37.620
I'm training and everything. I returned
after seven months and Mourinho...

00:30:37.816 --> 00:30:42.816
Trust? -... had trust in me
to play right away. He put me in.

00:30:43.032 --> 00:30:48.268
I started playing and I said "wow."
Something is not right.

00:30:48.660 --> 00:30:54.820
I didn't feel free,
I didn't feel strong... -Powerful, yes.

00:30:55.020 --> 00:30:59.580
I didn't feel like Ibra.
When Ibra plays, he lifts his leg here...

00:31:00.500 --> 00:31:04.500
I was afraid to lift my leg here.
When I leaned on the operated leg,

00:31:04.660 --> 00:31:08.300
I would collapse immediately.
-Yes, yes. -I didn't feel strong,

00:31:08.500 --> 00:31:11.380
but everything was fine.
There were no problems.

00:31:11.580 --> 00:31:14.460
Mentally, I wasn't there.

00:31:14.660 --> 00:31:22.670
When you operate on a knee, that knee
is like new and must be taught again.

00:31:23.979 --> 00:31:30.620
I told Mourinho not to put me in.
I went against my own ego.

00:31:31.140 --> 00:31:36.140
I wanted to play, I know I'm better
than the rest, but don't put me in.

00:31:36.340 --> 00:31:39.980
I can't help you because of
how I feel right now.

00:31:40.180 --> 00:31:46.140
I have to go slowly... It was January
or February in the Premier League.

00:31:46.340 --> 00:31:51.260
It's not like Serie A,
take it slow, or like La Liga.

00:31:51.940 --> 00:31:56.460
When you get the ball,
a player is there to hit you.

00:31:57.060 --> 00:32:01.020
If you aren't ready, it's over.

00:32:01.500 --> 00:32:06.940
I told him to keep me on the bench,
to give me more time to train.

00:32:08.180 --> 00:32:13.620
Another month passed
and I still wasn't ready.

00:32:13.820 --> 00:32:17.900
If I can't help, don't put me in.
Ibrahimović...

00:32:18.620 --> 00:32:20.860
It's not good for you or for me.

00:32:21.060 --> 00:32:27.333
My name is at the top and
ending like this isn't right.

00:32:27.540 --> 00:32:31.020
I told Mourinho that
I had a chance to go to America.

00:32:31.220 --> 00:32:36.900
I asked him to let me go
and try to play there.

00:32:37.100 --> 00:32:42.060
That's my chance to show
if I can still play or not.

00:32:42.300 --> 00:32:47.940
He told me to go, no problem.
He said I didn't even have to ask.

00:32:48.140 --> 00:32:52.860
It's the least he could do
because of what I did for him.

00:32:53.060 --> 00:32:59.500
Respect. -It was January.
I went to America.

00:32:59.780 --> 00:33:04.484
In America, I started from zero.
Like I told you about the coaches.

00:33:04.675 --> 00:33:07.235
To see if you can. -The coach
starts from zero, I start from zero.

00:33:07.450 --> 00:33:11.810
They asked me how I was.
I didn't know. But they...

00:33:13.500 --> 00:33:22.292
From the highest paid in the world,
I came to the budget there.

00:33:22.495 --> 00:33:26.620
There is a salary cap there.
I wasn't a DP, how do you say...

00:33:26.817 --> 00:33:30.120
One of the three who can get more.
-Who can earn more. -I didn't get that.

00:33:30.331 --> 00:33:35.100
It was all set. That's done
before the season starts. -Done.

00:33:35.300 --> 00:33:41.180
We were... I had a salary,
but I wasn't worried about it.

00:33:41.380 --> 00:33:46.620
I just said... How do you say?
Protection... -That's it.

00:33:46.782 --> 00:33:49.942
Just to be in the club. I don't need
a salary, I don't want anything.

00:33:50.159 --> 00:33:52.799
They asked me how I was.
I don't know.

00:33:53.007 --> 00:33:56.967
I'll come to you for free. No need
to pay. -You needed a platform

00:33:57.159 --> 00:34:00.879
to see if you could still play.
-To understand where I stand.

00:34:01.103 --> 00:34:06.143
I started playing the first game,
I score two goals.

00:34:06.311 --> 00:34:10.791
Like I was the old Ibra,
but the situation wasn't like that.

00:34:10.968 --> 00:34:14.648
Adrenaline, like I told you.
There was adrenaline, a little luck,

00:34:14.828 --> 00:34:22.703
a little instinct. But... Bit by bit...
We played there once a week.

00:34:22.967 --> 00:34:27.007
We played, we got a little time
and then we play again. -You have time

00:34:27.269 --> 00:34:31.560
to prepare and heal the knee. -To
prepare and see how the knee reacts.

00:34:32.740 --> 00:34:38.460
I didn't play on grass, but on plastic.
-Artificial grass, yes.

00:34:39.060 --> 00:34:43.420
I said it's not that I don't want to,
but I don't know how the knee will react.

00:34:43.660 --> 00:34:47.420
You can't play on artificial turf.
-In a year I was recovered.

00:34:47.660 --> 00:34:54.620
I signed for another year.
From the lowest salary in MLS, to the best.

00:34:55.140 --> 00:35:01.500
Ibra is back. I'll play another year.
I felt that I wanted to play.

00:35:02.700 --> 00:35:10.860
Stay or not? Mino says... I said
before when I finish my career,

00:35:11.100 --> 00:35:18.940
I want it to be at the top. Then
Mino told me if I want to finish at top,

00:35:19.180 --> 00:35:25.220
I must return to Europe. In Europe
I should finish my career, not in America.

00:35:25.580 --> 00:35:31.740
In America, small players finish. If you
are great, you'll return to Europe. -True.

00:35:31.940 --> 00:35:37.140
I was supposed to go to Napoli,
because Ancelotti was in Napoli.

00:35:37.420 --> 00:35:43.140
On the day I was supposed to sign,
Napoli fired Ancelotti.

00:35:43.780 --> 00:35:51.712
It wasn't OK for me. I went there for
Ancelotti, I know our relationship is top.

00:35:52.700 --> 00:36:02.540
It wasn't about the contract. When you
are 38, 39, 40, the contract isn't important.

00:36:03.020 --> 00:36:13.340
You must gather adrenaline for challenge.
I asked Mino who needs me the most.

00:36:15.420 --> 00:36:22.540
Two days before that, Milan loses 5-0
from Atalanta. They were in 11th place.

00:36:22.740 --> 00:36:27.180
He told me Milan. I asked why.
He said that I am the only one

00:36:27.380 --> 00:36:33.300
who can bring Milan back to the top.
Now he gave me fuel. -Bravo.

00:36:33.500 --> 00:36:38.660
He gave me what I needed to go.
When you are 38, 39 years old,

00:36:38.860 --> 00:36:42.700
you don't wake up every day full
of enthusiasm. -When you're a kid, yes.

00:36:42.902 --> 00:36:47.702
Every day is hard. Why am I
doing this? Why do I need this?

00:36:47.957 --> 00:36:52.517
I don't need it. But, in my head
is that I must bring Milan back.

00:36:52.780 --> 00:37:01.580
I go to them and first question at press
conference was what kind of benefits

00:37:01.860 --> 00:37:06.140
the club will have when I return,
because it can only be worse.

00:37:06.252 --> 00:37:09.559
That's how it is. When you do something
good, next time can only be worse.

00:37:09.671 --> 00:37:11.791
You can't go back again, yes,
to where you were.

00:37:11.968 --> 00:37:19.382
I say I never lost the passion
for what I do. For football.

00:37:19.809 --> 00:37:21.409
Since then...

00:37:22.780 --> 00:37:28.020
That's right. -Great. Tell me this,
to go back to America for a moment.

00:37:28.260 --> 00:37:33.220
One of... When you read something,
then it can sound arrogant.

00:37:33.460 --> 00:37:39.100
I am a god. In anything.
I am the best.

00:37:39.260 --> 00:37:46.980
However, when you look at that, you always
have a smile. You always have...

00:37:47.580 --> 00:37:54.420
You always laugh so you always
leave room to... -Melt in.

00:37:54.700 --> 00:38:00.580
It's a bit of a joke. Even if they ask
what Helena got from you,

00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:04.340
you say she got Zlatan.
-That's more serious. -Alright.

00:38:04.631 --> 00:38:10.904
Humor is a big part of you. Why
I ask and why I link it to America?

00:38:11.540 --> 00:38:19.660
Those ideas of yours to take that page in
the paper and write: "LA, you're welcome."

00:38:19.860 --> 00:38:27.020
And the thing with LeBron to return jersey.
Is that you? Is it some... -Me, me.

00:38:27.220 --> 00:38:36.940
Me. For that "You're welcome",
I gave myself to America.

00:38:37.140 --> 00:38:41.740
That was it. -That's a great joke.
-They didn't buy themselves a gift.

00:38:41.980 --> 00:38:49.540
It wasn't Christmas time. I brought
the gift to them in America. -Yes.

00:38:49.740 --> 00:38:51.860
I just wrote "You're welcome".

00:38:52.100 --> 00:38:59.020
That's all. With LeBron it was...
He made 23 jerseys and they called it

00:38:59.220 --> 00:39:08.545
"The Chosen One". He chose 23
athletes in LA and I got that jersey.

00:39:09.500 --> 00:39:15.340
I said if he wants to show respect,
to bring the jersey personally.

00:39:15.620 --> 00:39:21.939
First. Second, who are you to say that
I am "The Chosen One". I can say that.

00:39:22.220 --> 00:39:25.860
I signed the jersey
and returned it to him.

00:39:27.020 --> 00:39:31.740
That's crazy, you know. -And when I say
god, I... -That is terribly intelligent.

00:39:31.980 --> 00:39:37.660
When I play... Well, religion and
the rest, all that we put aside.

00:39:37.860 --> 00:39:40.900
When I play, I feel that
I am at the top.

00:39:41.140 --> 00:39:44.860
When I score goals,
what do I do with my hands?

00:39:45.100 --> 00:39:50.900
I feel alive. That is for me...
Proof that I am alive.

00:39:51.100 --> 00:39:53.860
It's not because of cameras or acting.

00:39:54.100 --> 00:39:57.340
That's how I feel, that's how
I am on the field.

00:39:57.540 --> 00:40:02.220
In that moment I feel
that I am alive.

00:40:02.422 --> 00:40:05.662
That is everything to me
at that moment. -Bravo.

00:40:05.893 --> 00:40:09.173
Tell me... -That's why
I think all players...

00:40:09.460 --> 00:40:13.660
They say that 50% is in the head,
but I think it is more than 50%.

00:40:13.860 --> 00:40:16.460
Surely, surely. -That is it.

00:40:16.700 --> 00:40:21.780
Tell me, with all this, all these
magnificent clubs you played for,

00:40:21.980 --> 00:40:26.900
you also played for Sweden, of course.
-Yes. -Though you often proudly point out

00:40:27.100 --> 00:40:32.500
the Balkan part of you, you always say
I am 100% Swedish and that's how it is.

00:40:32.700 --> 00:40:36.460
You were the captain, the best
scorer in history and all that.

00:40:36.660 --> 00:40:41.020
Sweden was always at the big
tournaments, but it was never

00:40:41.220 --> 00:40:46.940
good enough to make a
major result, right? OK.

00:40:47.180 --> 00:40:54.180
But what interests us here,
especially Bosnia and Croatia.

00:40:54.380 --> 00:40:58.940
It was always rumored... For example,
when I was the head coach,

00:40:59.540 --> 00:41:06.860
people from the top told me a hundred
times that they were two days late,

00:41:07.060 --> 00:41:13.740
the fax was late... -To play for...
-Those were the stories, Croatia for mom,

00:41:13.940 --> 00:41:22.460
Bosnia for dad. Was that ever realistic?
-I had a Bosnian and Swedish passport.

00:41:22.660 --> 00:41:28.180
I chose to play for Sweden,
they asked... Croatia and Bosnia,

00:41:28.380 --> 00:41:31.980
no one specifically asked for me.

00:41:32.220 --> 00:41:36.780
There were stories, but nothing
concrete. Sweden was there.

00:41:37.060 --> 00:41:43.740
I played for Sweden until I was 16.
Then I didn't play, then for the under-21

00:41:44.180 --> 00:41:50.260
I played seven games, six goals.
After that I made  the step

00:41:50.460 --> 00:41:55.660
to the first team, but no one
specifically asked. -And if they had?

00:41:55.860 --> 00:41:58.460
Would there have been a chance?
-There'd be a chance to

00:41:58.581 --> 00:42:01.761
win the World Cup and
European Championship.

00:42:05.260 --> 00:42:09.100
But I don't know if that would be
for Croatia or for Bosnia.

00:42:09.230 --> 00:42:12.310
I think the chances would be higher
for Croatia, given the team they had.

00:42:12.557 --> 00:42:18.917
Not because you are here. I mean
because of the team. Šuker, Bokšić.

00:42:19.420 --> 00:42:26.300
Croatia was missing a striker.
Everyone else had top ones.

00:42:27.060 --> 00:42:34.580
Respect to all, Mandžukić, Olić, Rebić...
-You mean after Šuker and Bokšić?

00:42:34.820 --> 00:42:41.620
After them. -After them, yes, yes.
-If they played, there'd be competition.

00:42:43.020 --> 00:42:47.260
So, there would be a chance?
OK, great. -But it was never concrete.

00:42:47.460 --> 00:42:52.340
It never was, no, no.
I can tell you that. -Is that possible?

00:42:53.260 --> 00:42:58.860
It's a pleasure talking to you.
-Thanks a lot. -Thanks for your time.

00:42:59.026 --> 00:43:05.546
Trophies in all leagues. Only England
and USA are missing. -Champions League,

00:43:06.020 --> 00:43:15.980
Premier League... -And MLS. -It's interesting
that everyone says I was an ego player,

00:43:16.180 --> 00:43:21.060
an individualist, but I have 34
collective trophies.

00:43:21.420 --> 00:43:27.060
If you’ve won 34 trophies
in the biggest leagues in Europe,

00:43:27.300 --> 00:43:32.580
and Europe is the center of football,
it’s impossible to say you’re selfish.

00:43:32.820 --> 00:43:37.740
When two players are through on goal,
the one who shoots is called selfish,

00:43:37.900 --> 00:43:43.389
the one who passes is praised.
-Right. -I had three or four…

00:43:43.531 --> 00:43:48.045
Okay, Messi passed me later on,
I’m talking about the earlier years.

00:43:48.193 --> 00:43:51.374
Maxwell and Dani Alves as well,
but not by much.

00:43:51.556 --> 00:43:56.038
Yes, but those were clubs that hadn’t won
anything before you arrived.

00:43:56.161 --> 00:43:58.971
So you join Inter, who weren’t
champions at the time, Milan too.

00:43:59.120 --> 00:44:01.866
Immediately. They had their own story,
but this happened right away.

00:44:02.140 --> 00:44:04.260
Inter hadn’t been champions for 17 years.

00:44:04.500 --> 00:44:06.220
Juventus hadn’t won
for one or two years either,

00:44:06.500 --> 00:44:10.620
and then we won together. -Paris…
-The only real "machine"

00:44:10.860 --> 00:44:13.220
that was already winning
when I joined them was Barcelona.

00:44:13.460 --> 00:44:18.540
That was a machine. Paris was a project,
Milan hadn’t won for two years,

00:44:18.780 --> 00:44:25.180
Inter for 17 years… -And that leaves
two things, if you really look at it,

00:44:26.660 --> 00:44:30.620
two things are missing.
Two main things.

00:44:30.860 --> 00:44:34.820
You scored a huge number of…
You were named

00:44:35.060 --> 00:44:40.140
Swedish Footballer of the Year 12 times,
10 of them in a row. -Yes, yes.

00:44:40.420 --> 00:44:46.100
That’s incredible. And you’ve won
so many individual awards.

00:44:46.540 --> 00:44:52.420
You’re missing the Champions League, right?
And the Ballon d’Or.

00:44:57.300 --> 00:45:02.580
You’ve said a few times that you believe
you deserved the Ballon d’Or.

00:45:02.780 --> 00:45:09.291
Is there a particular season
when you think you should have won it?

00:45:10.540 --> 00:45:15.500
It all depends on the Champions League,
which is a team trophy.

00:45:15.630 --> 00:45:18.391
I think if you win the Champions League,
you’ll also win the Ballon d’Or.

00:45:18.465 --> 00:45:20.145
So that’s what you’re missing.

00:45:20.322 --> 00:45:22.882
One thing leads to another.
-It pushes the other.

00:45:23.082 --> 00:45:25.251
Yeah, it pushes the other.
That’s how I see it.

00:45:25.412 --> 00:45:28.024
Although some players have won it
without winning the Champions League.

00:45:28.159 --> 00:45:32.688
But then you had to have a strong
national team. -It wasn’t always like that.

00:45:32.875 --> 00:45:34.595
When Ribéry should have won,
he didn’t,

00:45:34.771 --> 00:45:37.243
even though he won the Champions League.
-That’s true.

00:45:37.984 --> 00:45:43.055
So that rule doesn’t always apply.
I think it also depends on

00:45:43.260 --> 00:45:47.740
which national team you play for,
which club you come from,

00:45:47.940 --> 00:45:54.340
and how much attention
you give to marketing…

00:45:55.580 --> 00:46:01.020
In my opinion, the Ballon d’Or
is an individual award,

00:46:01.260 --> 00:46:06.660
for the player who made the biggest
individual difference on the pitch.

00:46:06.769 --> 00:46:09.010
The Champions League is the team trophy.

00:46:09.135 --> 00:46:13.515
This year Dembélé won it,
but who was actually better individually?

00:46:13.748 --> 00:46:18.624
Vinícius was better. -Yamal.
-Yamal too, but he’s young.

00:46:18.781 --> 00:46:21.733
It doesn’t matter that he’s young.
Age doesn’t matter here.

00:46:21.874 --> 00:46:24.780
You can’t tell me you wouldn’t give him
a chance just because he’s 17. -Alright.

00:46:24.862 --> 00:46:26.422
Age doesn’t matter here.

00:46:26.522 --> 00:46:30.335
You don’t need to be 20 to play.
If you’re ready, you’re ready.

00:46:30.527 --> 00:46:35.085
Okay, Yamal, if you’re ready,
go and beat Inter. Beat Inter.

00:46:35.564 --> 00:46:37.718
And he was the best individually.
He destroyed Inter.

00:46:37.834 --> 00:46:40.225
Give me one more of those…
take me to the final.

00:46:40.733 --> 00:46:44.530
So, do you have to win the Champions League
to win the Ballon d’Or?

00:46:44.721 --> 00:46:50.121
No, but it’s a huge boost.
-It helps a lot, yes.

00:46:50.339 --> 00:46:52.379
But I’m talking about
who was the best individually.

00:46:52.540 --> 00:46:54.788
I agree with your theory.
-Because it’s an individual award.

00:46:54.910 --> 00:46:56.310
I agree, yes.

00:46:56.651 --> 00:47:01.671
There were periods in my career
when I was individually the best,

00:47:01.879 --> 00:47:05.159
when I made the difference,
but I didn’t win the Champions League.

00:47:05.435 --> 00:47:09.647
Still, I made the difference individually
and was the best.

00:47:09.920 --> 00:47:19.538
But not everyone liked
my character, my behavior, my style,

00:47:20.060 --> 00:47:28.620
which I think is important for a team,
but personally it didn’t bother me.

00:47:28.860 --> 00:47:32.100
Personally, yes. -So the best player
doesn’t always win it.

00:47:32.543 --> 00:47:35.524
I always say my mentality

00:47:35.722 --> 00:47:40.642
and who I am wouldn’t change
if I won that award.

00:47:41.140 --> 00:47:45.894
It wouldn’t affect my career. -Of course.
-Would I have liked to win it?

00:47:45.988 --> 00:47:47.748
Yes, a hundred times.

00:47:47.838 --> 00:47:50.190
To win the Champions League?
Yes, a hundred times.

00:47:50.377 --> 00:47:53.377
But it wouldn’t change me as a player.

00:47:53.570 --> 00:47:58.612
It’s just a moment of happiness.
It shouldn’t change a player.

00:47:58.726 --> 00:48:01.126
A player always remains who he is.

00:48:01.411 --> 00:48:10.097
That’s why I say that, as a striker,
I was complete. I could do everything.

00:48:11.380 --> 00:48:14.980
Everything, nothing was missing.
-That’s for sure.

00:48:15.157 --> 00:48:19.157
Other strikers score 100 goals.
I could have scored 100 too.

00:48:19.833 --> 00:48:22.593
So does that mean Bokšić wasn’t good
because he scored eight goals?

00:48:22.785 --> 00:48:25.345
Haaland is much better
than someone who scored 50.

00:48:25.523 --> 00:48:27.923
Those eight back then
are like 50 today. -Yes, yes.

00:48:28.082 --> 00:48:29.990
That’s what I’m saying.

00:48:30.173 --> 00:48:34.092
Today’s generations are different.
That’s how I see it.

00:48:34.317 --> 00:48:43.225
I’m the most complete striker of all time.
Left foot, right foot, headers, everything.

00:48:43.375 --> 00:48:44.654
Intelligent…

00:48:44.775 --> 00:48:49.881
That’s why, in my opinion,
you deserved the Ballon d’Or.

00:48:50.012 --> 00:48:52.372
You’re a player who deserved
the Ballon d’Or,

00:48:52.503 --> 00:48:54.864
and I’m not saying this
just because you’re here…

00:48:54.983 --> 00:49:01.108
There are stronger players than you,
faster ones, guys with better dribbling,

00:49:01.245 --> 00:49:04.765
a better shot, but no one
has all of that in one.

00:49:04.917 --> 00:49:08.117
And you do. You’re what I like to call…

00:49:08.249 --> 00:49:13.609
There isn’t a goal at this level
that someone has scored

00:49:13.706 --> 00:49:15.811
that you haven’t scored yourself. -Yes.

00:49:16.008 --> 00:49:19.008
Maybe not straight from a corner,
since you don’t take them, right?

00:49:19.153 --> 00:49:22.748
And maybe not from your own half.
-I didn’t score just one of those,

00:49:22.900 --> 00:49:28.700
I scored more than one, which is insane.
-Messi scored 20, 30, even 50 goals

00:49:28.900 --> 00:49:33.060
after dribbling past four or five players,
and you did that too at Ajax, right,

00:49:33.300 --> 00:49:38.060
when you went past all of them.
But no one scored goals like you.

00:49:38.312 --> 00:49:43.512
A free-kick rocket, a tap-in like Inzaghi,
a header like Andy Carroll…

00:49:43.790 --> 00:49:48.230
Everything, and on top of that,
the spectacular ones.

00:49:48.376 --> 00:49:54.016
In England from 30 meters, bicycle kicks,
that goal to Italy at the Euro,

00:49:54.272 --> 00:49:58.512
that last goal in MLS
when you lift your leg like that…

00:49:59.120 --> 00:50:01.238
Did you know that only you
and Cristiano Ronaldo

00:50:01.350 --> 00:50:03.550
have scored a goal
in every single minute of a match?

00:50:03.687 --> 00:50:05.887
There’s one more player.
There are three of us.

00:50:06.009 --> 00:50:09.287
I think it’s Suárez.
-Kane? No? -I think it’s Suárez.

00:50:09.360 --> 00:50:11.881
There are three of us.
I saw that stat somewhere.

00:50:12.046 --> 00:50:14.566
Yes, yes. By the way, just to say,

00:50:14.719 --> 00:50:18.879
Bokšić scored more than eight goals
in France, at Marseille.

00:50:19.000 --> 00:50:22.811
No, I meant that generation and Serie A.
Maradona, how many did he score?

00:50:22.934 --> 00:50:25.194
Ten, fifteen? -Yeah, it was
tougher back then.

00:50:25.307 --> 00:50:27.467
I’m not saying he only scored eight…

00:50:27.636 --> 00:50:33.584
I’m just saying that the numbers back then
are like today’s numbers. -100%.

00:50:33.721 --> 00:50:37.272
The game was different.
-Like basketball. -Yes, same thing.

00:50:37.460 --> 00:50:42.860
I’m just saying that the goals
they scored in that era

00:50:43.037 --> 00:50:45.917
are worth the same as
50 goals today. -For sure.

00:50:46.070 --> 00:50:48.070
One isn’t better than the other.

00:50:48.216 --> 00:50:51.056
They gave their best
under those conditions,

00:50:51.162 --> 00:50:54.319
just like players do today,
maybe even more.

00:50:54.479 --> 00:51:00.514
Bokšić, in my opinion, was top class.
I love tall, complete players.

00:51:00.667 --> 00:51:04.827
I’m 197 cm tall, and when I move
on the pitch, I don’t move like this,

00:51:05.060 --> 00:51:09.220
I move like this, elegantly.
I like elegant players. -Yes, yes.

00:51:09.380 --> 00:51:15.700
When I’m on the pitch,
I see the game three steps ahead.

00:51:15.869 --> 00:51:17.869
If the play goes there,
I know the ball will end up here,

00:51:18.055 --> 00:51:20.135
that’s how I think.

00:51:20.460 --> 00:51:23.260
I don’t run there
just so I can get the ball here.

00:51:23.453 --> 00:51:30.453
I think three moves ahead,
but I don’t think I’m some kind of genius,

00:51:30.661 --> 00:51:33.981
that’s just how I played,
and I showed it on the pitch.

00:51:34.220 --> 00:51:44.340
I was 197 cm, 95 kilos when I played,
but I moved like I wasn’t. -Unreal agility.

00:51:44.580 --> 00:51:51.260
That’s why I love tall players
who can do extraordinary things.

00:51:51.540 --> 00:51:55.820
Like Zidane, Bokšić, you.
-Athletes. -That’s undeniable.

00:51:56.020 --> 00:51:58.860
Tell me, how would you
describe your character?

00:51:59.060 --> 00:52:04.672
You always say that the two most important
things are faith and discipline.

00:52:06.260 --> 00:52:10.700
On the cover of your book, you say:
"Believe in yourself.

00:52:10.927 --> 00:52:13.927
There’s nothing wrong with
being different from others.

00:52:14.260 --> 00:52:18.420
If you’re not like everyone else."

00:52:18.998 --> 00:52:23.518
And yet, you emphasize
the Balkan in yourself.

00:52:23.680 --> 00:52:28.520
When you say "Balkan,"
what do you mean? -Balkan because,

00:52:28.860 --> 00:52:33.100
even though I was born in Sweden,
a typical Swede isn’t

00:52:33.300 --> 00:52:35.980
what Zlatan Ibrahimović is.

00:52:38.442 --> 00:52:45.794
How can I put it…
I don’t look like a typical Swede.

00:52:46.540 --> 00:52:53.780
Blue eyes, blond hair… I have a big nose,
Swedes don’t, Balkans do.

00:52:54.460 --> 00:53:04.346
I’m Balkan in how I react,
I’m temperamental. -Passion…

00:53:04.700 --> 00:53:09.275
That’s what makes me different from
the rest. -And you mean patience too.

00:53:09.465 --> 00:53:11.908
We grew up in a family,
in an environment that

00:53:12.041 --> 00:53:14.831
others might have seen as aggressive,
but to us, it was normal.

00:53:15.009 --> 00:53:22.488
A Swede is softer than a Balkan.
Although some Balkans are soft too.

00:53:22.864 --> 00:53:31.074
I’m just saying I didn’t do things
the way a typical Swede would.

00:53:32.342 --> 00:53:33.822
I’m different.

00:53:33.966 --> 00:53:37.646
You’re very empathetic,
you care about the people around you,

00:53:37.918 --> 00:53:42.998
you take great care of your family,
even of Maxwell.

00:53:43.880 --> 00:53:45.249
Max is very soft.

00:53:45.419 --> 00:53:50.059
He’s a great player, but you always
made sure he was treated just as well.

00:53:50.275 --> 00:53:54.795
There’s a story, I don’t know
if it’s true, probably is.

00:53:55.700 --> 00:54:01.580
When you were a kid in Rosengård,
when your mom went to work,

00:54:01.820 --> 00:54:07.340
if you were hungry, a Swedish lady
would make you sandwiches.

00:54:07.940 --> 00:54:14.260
And when you made it in your
career later, you gave her a check.

00:54:14.366 --> 00:54:16.426
It’s not about the check,
it’s that you don’t forget

00:54:16.538 --> 00:54:18.293
the people who were good to you.

00:54:18.417 --> 00:54:22.537
Where I was born
and where I come from,

00:54:22.676 --> 00:54:25.725
people don’t forget
what has happened to them.

00:54:25.876 --> 00:54:28.686
That’s why I told you,
I won’t change for anyone.

00:54:28.884 --> 00:54:34.201
Even if my financial situation changes
or if I become famous,

00:54:34.433 --> 00:54:39.393
I’ll never forget where I come from.
That’s the most important thing.

00:54:39.624 --> 00:54:44.544
People start to lose themselves
because of fame and money

00:54:44.980 --> 00:54:48.940
and forget where they came from.
-For sure. -I’m not like that.

00:54:49.140 --> 00:54:56.940
I’ve been on both sides.
In poverty and in wealth.

00:54:57.300 --> 00:55:02.140
In poverty, where I had nothing,
and in wealth, where I have everything.

00:55:02.340 --> 00:55:06.820
I’ve been on both sides
and I know what it’s like on each.

00:55:07.100 --> 00:55:13.428
I’ve been in a situation where
I couldn’t buy what I wanted to eat,

00:55:13.980 --> 00:55:20.380
and now I can buy everything I want.

00:55:20.540 --> 00:55:26.020
That’s true. I can buy whatever I want
and I have no limits.

00:55:26.260 --> 00:55:29.260
But I haven’t forgotten
where I come from.

00:55:29.500 --> 00:55:36.580
And I know I could survive
if I went back there. -Bravo.

00:55:36.820 --> 00:55:40.180
The worst thing is forgetting
where you came from,

00:55:40.420 --> 00:55:43.780
then you’re not being realistic.

00:55:43.980 --> 00:55:48.260
Because what you have now
might not be there one day.

00:55:48.460 --> 00:55:52.820
Of course. And to finish,
let’s talk a little about family.

00:55:53.500 --> 00:55:57.300
You’ve mentioned her
a few times, Helena…

00:55:58.420 --> 00:56:03.780
A Swede who was already
an accomplished woman before you.

00:56:03.980 --> 00:56:08.660
She had her own career…
-Not everyone knows that, but it’s true.

00:56:08.900 --> 00:56:19.140
There are situations where people build
their careers through certain players.

00:56:19.380 --> 00:56:22.835
She already had her career before me.

00:56:23.371 --> 00:56:30.401
She says she fed me as a little boy,
before I ever fed her,

00:56:31.482 --> 00:56:35.877
because she had a career before me.
-Yes, she fed you before you fed her.

00:56:36.118 --> 00:56:40.338
She took care of me before
I ever took care of her. -Yes.

00:56:40.980 --> 00:56:45.541
Because she already had a career
and she’s ten years older than me.

00:56:45.706 --> 00:56:53.938
Yes, I know. -I think that’s
the reason for our success.

00:56:55.731 --> 00:57:03.952
What happened to me,
she had already experienced,

00:57:04.460 --> 00:57:10.862
she had been through it,
she was more mature and had patience.

00:57:12.846 --> 00:57:19.305
She was mentally ready
for what was happening to me.

00:57:19.423 --> 00:57:21.423
She was ready for you, yes.

00:57:21.547 --> 00:57:26.704
If a woman my age had been next to me,
she would have been completely lost. -True.

00:57:27.000 --> 00:57:32.727
Maybe it would have, but she wouldn’t
have been able to control me or protect me.

00:57:32.993 --> 00:57:37.727
She wouldn’t have been able to
protect you. -So that I could feel good.

00:57:37.925 --> 00:57:41.875
I understand you.
-I think I was lucky to meet Helena.

00:57:42.001 --> 00:57:44.602
Well done. You have two sons.
-That’s right, we have two sons.

00:57:44.735 --> 00:57:47.899
Maximilian and Vincent,
who are teenagers.

00:57:48.624 --> 00:57:51.144
You mentioned it yourself earlier...

00:57:51.307 --> 00:57:55.070
How do you and Helena agree
on raising them, considering that you

00:57:55.210 --> 00:57:57.218
grew up in different circumstances?

00:57:57.411 --> 00:58:01.469
Completely different circumstances.
-How do you manage parenting? -Well.

00:58:01.689 --> 00:58:11.098
When it comes to parenting,
I don’t think I’m too strict. -Yes.

00:58:11.274 --> 00:58:13.938
And I’m not one of those parents
who constantly tell them what to do.

00:58:14.036 --> 00:58:15.750
We are equally involved
in raising them.

00:58:15.880 --> 00:58:21.157
She helps with what she’s good at,
and I help as much as I can too.

00:58:21.940 --> 00:58:27.578
However, I’m more the one who
criticizes them. -You criticize them.

00:58:28.404 --> 00:58:30.352
When bad things happen.

00:58:30.560 --> 00:58:34.633
I think it’s better that I’m like that,
because when children feel

00:58:34.797 --> 00:58:37.655
the need to talk about emotions,
it’s better they talk to their mother.

00:58:37.829 --> 00:58:41.336
Of course, a mother is a mother.
-When it comes to me, things are clear.

00:58:41.466 --> 00:58:43.986
With me, everything is black or white.
There’s nothing in between.

00:58:44.132 --> 00:58:47.086
Either something is allowed
or it isn’t. -You give them security.

00:58:47.492 --> 00:58:53.047
I can’t be different, because I didn’t
grow up in that kind of environment.

00:58:53.229 --> 00:58:55.349
If something happens and they
start crying, I’m not the one

00:58:55.518 --> 00:58:57.558
who comes and hugs them.

00:58:57.820 --> 00:59:01.180
I understand you. -I tell them,
"Go to your mother, let her hug you."

00:59:01.420 --> 00:59:04.460
If it happens that they cry
in my presence,

00:59:04.590 --> 00:59:09.430
the only thing I can say is:
"Stop crying or go to another room."

00:59:09.623 --> 00:59:12.023
That’s it. -Well done.
-That’s just how I am.

00:59:12.168 --> 00:59:14.088
I don’t know any other way.
-Well done.

00:59:16.380 --> 00:59:22.460
Do you ever think, when you see
how they’re being raised...

00:59:23.140 --> 00:59:30.419
Do you ever think it would be better
to raise them the way you were raised

00:59:30.896 --> 00:59:36.294
when you lived in Rosengård?
-Would that be better for them? -Yes.

00:59:40.340 --> 00:59:42.794
It’s not easy to talk about.

00:59:42.932 --> 00:59:46.676
I don’t have a clear answer
to that question,

00:59:46.997 --> 00:59:50.558
because we all grow up
in different circumstances.

00:59:51.220 --> 00:59:56.420
What they have now and what they
think is best for them,

00:59:56.660 --> 01:00:01.380
I felt the same way
when I was their age.

01:00:01.820 --> 01:00:08.020
When I was their age, that was
my maximum, what I could achieve.

01:00:08.340 --> 01:00:11.300
One of my sons recently passed
his driving test and has a car.

01:00:11.460 --> 01:00:14.676
When I was his age, I didn’t have
a car. I had to earn it first.

01:00:14.787 --> 01:00:17.559
When I started earning money,
I bought it only after a year.

01:00:17.857 --> 01:00:25.530
As a parent, I try to balance
and decide what’s right and what isn’t.

01:00:26.297 --> 01:00:30.017
At the same time, you want them
to learn something,

01:00:30.303 --> 01:00:32.742
but not to suffer too much.
For me, that’s balance.

01:00:32.973 --> 01:00:37.453
Three things matter to me:
discipline, respect, and independence.

01:00:37.654 --> 01:00:41.454
That’s what’s most important.
They never get what they want.

01:00:41.677 --> 01:00:45.997
If they really want something,
they have to earn it.

01:00:46.308 --> 01:00:49.588
And they have to work hard
to get it. -I understand.

01:00:50.060 --> 01:00:51.860
That’s how I see it.

01:00:52.180 --> 01:00:56.500
If you’re asking whether I ever regret
not having some of the things

01:00:56.780 --> 01:01:01.020
they have today, my answer is no.
I think I had everything.

01:01:01.220 --> 01:01:04.260
Otherwise you wouldn’t have
achieved all these results.

01:01:04.460 --> 01:01:06.700
That I achieved everything
as an individual?

01:01:06.980 --> 01:01:11.180
If you had everything
your children have,

01:01:11.340 --> 01:01:16.022
do you think you would have
achieved all these results?

01:01:17.323 --> 01:01:23.008
Or do you think you need to be hungry
I don’t mean literal hunger. -I think...

01:01:23.380 --> 01:01:26.100
But to have something
that pushes you forward.

01:01:26.300 --> 01:01:29.980
Yes, I understand,
to have desire... -To succeed.

01:01:30.220 --> 01:01:35.174
I think each of us
has our own destiny.

01:01:35.541 --> 01:01:38.069
What happened to me
simply had to happen.

01:01:38.374 --> 01:01:40.780
And I had to achieve
all these results.

01:01:40.980 --> 01:01:45.180
Everything we talked about
influenced me to become who I am.

01:01:45.380 --> 01:01:47.260
They have their own path.

01:01:47.500 --> 01:01:50.660
If they want something,
it depends only on them.

01:01:51.020 --> 01:01:56.780
I will help you. I will give you...
How do you say it?

01:01:58.140 --> 01:02:06.410
Tools. Advice. -Both play football.
I told them...

01:02:07.460 --> 01:02:11.420
When they were starting out,
everything we did, football, school,

01:02:11.620 --> 01:02:15.260
they used their mother's last name.
Not Ibrahimovic.

01:02:15.460 --> 01:02:20.300
They used her last name.
We did that to protect them.

01:02:20.540 --> 01:02:25.220
They didn't know what the world was like.
At that age, they think the world is wow,

01:02:25.420 --> 01:02:30.860
everything is positive, everything is OK,
but it's not like that. It's not like that.

01:02:31.060 --> 01:02:37.730
When you carry the name Ibrahimovic,
there are positive and negative sides.

01:02:38.483 --> 01:02:50.376
They didn't grow up in their father's shadow.
-Yes, yes. -They are more important than me.

01:02:50.561 --> 01:02:57.149
Ibrahimović is a professional, a footballer.
In the house I'm just a father, not a player.

01:02:57.376 --> 01:03:06.408
I'm not a professional. I don't bring it home.
In my home, there are no photos of me.

01:03:06.900 --> 01:03:13.780
There is only one, from Sweden, in the...
How do you say? -The gym.

01:03:14.500 --> 01:03:22.020
A photo of my feet,
to not forget where I got everything I have.

01:03:22.260 --> 01:03:28.500
That is the only photo. There are no others.
I played for Milan... Nothing.

01:03:28.780 --> 01:03:40.258
They live their own lives. They must
grow up independent of Ibrahimović.

01:03:40.558 --> 01:03:46.318
I don't want them growing up with "my father".
No, no. They have their own story.

01:03:46.660 --> 01:03:54.810
They play football, I help them there.
With me, it is only black and white.

01:03:55.180 --> 01:03:59.100
Even if you're my son, if you're not good,
you're not good. -Bravo.

01:03:59.300 --> 01:04:02.180
I won't tell you that you are good
if you are not. -Yes, yes.

01:04:02.420 --> 01:04:10.310
I told them that I am disciplined.
In the beginning I drove them to training.

01:04:10.860 --> 01:04:15.420
My time with them when you are a player...
You are always in hotels, playing matches,

01:04:15.580 --> 01:04:18.700
you are never at home.
You don't have much time for the children.

01:04:18.940 --> 01:04:23.460
I spent time with the children
only when I drove them to school.

01:04:23.700 --> 01:04:28.660
Every morning at 7 I drove them to school.
Then I could be with them... -That's right.

01:04:28.860 --> 01:04:31.140
Then I would go to training.

01:04:31.540 --> 01:04:36.660
Then I would drive them to training.
They trained in the afternoon.

01:04:36.900 --> 01:04:45.655
Again, I drove them. I told
them that I drive them every day.

01:04:46.316 --> 01:04:54.460
I didn't want them to tell me they no longer
wanted to train, football or something else.

01:04:54.660 --> 01:05:00.378
I don't want you to tell me you don't
want to. I drive you every day.

01:05:01.034 --> 01:05:03.815
I have other obligations too.
I am with you then.

01:05:03.964 --> 01:05:08.111
When you get to training,
you're there 1-2 hrs.

01:05:08.260 --> 01:05:13.060
You must give 200%. That is for you.
I do this for you.

01:05:13.260 --> 01:05:19.300
If you don't give 200%
at training, I have other plans.

01:05:19.540 --> 01:05:25.700
I don't drive you for my sake,
but for yours. -Correct.

01:05:25.980 --> 01:05:31.940
That's when I am with them. I told
them they can do other things,

01:05:32.140 --> 01:05:36.140
but when they train, they must give 200%.
Do not waste your time here

01:05:36.340 --> 01:05:40.260
and then later say you want something else.
Then we must do something else.

01:05:40.740 --> 01:05:49.740
I explained that to them and
then they did it for themselves.

01:05:50.100 --> 01:05:54.260
I told them if you're going to do this
for me, stop immediately.

01:05:55.108 --> 01:05:56.649
I told them...

01:05:57.288 --> 01:06:04.761
If something happens to you, it will be
because of you, not me. -Yes.

01:06:05.820 --> 01:06:14.540
We have an academy called
Vismara, and Milanello is the first team.

01:06:15.500 --> 01:06:22.500
They went there for a trial. If they're OK,
they'll be accepted. They were accepted.

01:06:22.780 --> 01:06:29.630
For three years, I didn't go there.
I said, I don't want to...

01:06:32.198 --> 01:06:35.080
I didn’t want it to seem
like they were there because of me.

01:06:35.304 --> 01:06:39.470
Because of you, right? -Yes.
And that didn’t sit quite right with me.

01:06:39.616 --> 01:06:44.461
I’m their father, I want to see them play.
But for three years, I didn’t go there.

01:06:44.672 --> 01:06:47.492
I said, "You need to earn
the right to be here."

01:06:47.640 --> 01:06:49.768
You need to earn it for yourselves.

01:06:50.091 --> 01:06:55.445
I don’t want you to have any privileges
and then have people talking about it.

01:06:55.584 --> 01:06:57.975
And now it’s the other way around,
basically in the world.

01:06:58.165 --> 01:07:01.539
Ibra goes out while you train.
And that’s exactly what I did.

01:07:01.665 --> 01:07:06.414
When they turned 16, they came to me
and said they wanted the surname Ibrahimović.

01:07:06.593 --> 01:07:13.398
I asked them, "Are you sure you want this?
Because the situation will change.

01:07:13.638 --> 01:07:16.478
Even though everyone knows
who you are, things will change."

01:07:16.670 --> 01:07:18.750
They said, "No, we’re aware of everything."

01:07:18.927 --> 01:07:21.327
And then they changed their surname
to Ibrahimović. -Phenomenal.

01:07:21.606 --> 01:07:26.366
I still have two more questions.
Since you’re mentioning Ibrahimović, Seger…

01:07:26.464 --> 01:07:30.031
Why did your jersey originally say "Zlatan,"
and when did you change it to "Ibrahimović"?

01:07:30.121 --> 01:07:31.201
Yes, yes.

01:07:31.380 --> 01:07:36.420
Do you remember when I first talked
about "Zlatan fever" in Sweden?

01:07:36.700 --> 01:07:39.540
In the newspapers, it always said
Zlatan, Zlatan…

01:07:39.700 --> 01:07:42.700
It never said Ibrahimović.
Zlatan, Zlatan…

01:07:43.780 --> 01:07:46.460
I was playing with Mido.

01:07:46.780 --> 01:07:52.300
His name isn’t Mido, it’s Ahmed Hossam,
but on his jersey it said Mido.

01:07:52.500 --> 01:07:54.620
When I spoke to him, I said:

01:07:54.780 --> 01:07:57.620
"If your jersey says Mido,
then mine will say Zlatan."

01:07:57.820 --> 01:08:00.660
But after three months,
I didn’t feel right about it.

01:08:00.940 --> 01:08:06.340
I said, "Zlatan represents me,
not my family."

01:08:06.540 --> 01:08:10.940
"I want to represent my family."
So I changed it to Ibrahimović.

01:08:11.140 --> 01:08:18.620
It was a momentary thing, because everyone
in Sweden was talking only about Zlatan,

01:08:18.820 --> 01:08:22.340
and I just simply thought
it would be cool.

01:08:22.540 --> 01:08:28.460
It wasn’t a big deal for long.
But immediately, I felt it wasn’t right.

01:08:28.539 --> 01:08:30.695
Because of your dad, right?
Well, it wasn’t really about that.

01:08:30.815 --> 01:08:33.281
Because of the Ibrahimović family,
I went with Ibrahimović.

01:08:33.462 --> 01:08:38.022
And the last question… Since this show
is for both kids and parents,

01:08:38.518 --> 01:08:44.798
I read somewhere that you
suggest kids try two sports.

01:08:45.029 --> 01:08:49.559
Yes, always. -One individual,
and one team sport. Like you.

01:08:49.667 --> 01:08:51.231
Explain that a little.

01:08:51.332 --> 01:08:57.312
When I was young , and I’m still young…
I played football as a team sport.

01:08:57.420 --> 01:09:03.260
So, you learn to have fun.
Or how do you say it? -Yes, to play.

01:09:03.500 --> 01:09:07.387
When you play a team sport,
you think collectively,

01:09:08.180 --> 01:09:14.660
you socialize, and you learn
how to build relationships

01:09:14.860 --> 01:09:20.140
with others, how to behave, how to react.

01:09:20.380 --> 01:09:23.740
In an individual sport, it’s just you.
I trained Taekwondo,

01:09:23.980 --> 01:09:29.174
which is an individual sport.
So you train self-discipline.

01:09:29.478 --> 01:09:33.431
Everything depends on you
how you control everything, individually,

01:09:33.580 --> 01:09:39.060
how you react individually.
In contrast, a team sport is different.

01:09:39.300 --> 01:09:44.060
They say school is important for kids.

01:09:44.460 --> 01:09:47.820
For me, school is important
so that young people

01:09:47.980 --> 01:09:50.500
learn to respect each other.

01:09:50.700 --> 01:09:56.340
To find each other, not just boys
and girls finding each other,

01:09:58.780 --> 01:10:02.460
but also to socialize.

01:10:02.740 --> 01:10:08.100
After that, you learn math,
English, and other important subjects.

01:10:08.260 --> 01:10:11.340
Everything else is someone else’s story,
and I don’t need that,

01:10:11.540 --> 01:10:16.300
because I want to create my own story
so that others can read it.

01:10:16.460 --> 01:10:18.540
That’s my mentality.

01:10:18.940 --> 01:10:22.140
But I tell my kids that school
is important so they learn

01:10:22.380 --> 01:10:25.340
to respect others and socialize.

01:10:25.540 --> 01:10:30.020
The same goes for sports. When you train
one team sport and one individual sport,

01:10:30.180 --> 01:10:32.180
in the end, they intertwine.

01:10:32.380 --> 01:10:37.680
And football, in the end, is individual too.
That’s important. -Bravo.

01:10:38.970 --> 01:10:40.730
Even though nowadays,
all of this is somehow getting lost.

01:10:40.805 --> 01:10:42.375
Thank you so much. -Thank you.

01:10:42.440 --> 01:10:45.586
Zlatan, I really enjoyed this.
Respect. -Thank you very much.

